@startuml fig-arp
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title ARP (IPv4): Resolving IP to MAC on a LAN

participant "Host A\nIP_A, MAC_A" as A #FFE0B2
participant "Switch" as SW #E3F2FD
participant "Host B\nIP_B, MAC_B" as B #C8E6C9
participant "Host C\nIP_C, MAC_C" as C #ECEFF1

A -[#1565C0]> SW : ARP Request (broadcast)\n"Who has IP_B? Tell MAC_A"
SW -[#1565C0]> B : broadcast delivered
SW -[#1565C0]> C : broadcast delivered

B -[#43A047]> SW : ARP Reply (unicast)\n"IP_B is at MAC_B"
SW -[#43A047]> A : unicast to MAC_A

== Host A caches IP_B → MAC_B ==

A -> B : Ethernet frame to MAC_B

legend right
  Step 1: Host A broadcasts an ARP request
  Step 2: Host B replies with its MAC (unicast)
  Step 3: Host A caches the mapping
  Host C ignores the request (not its IP)
endlegend
@enduml
